        <img src="../../../assets/images/pictures/fridge.jpg" alt="Refrigerator" style="width:400px; margin:20px 0;">

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>If your refrigerator is not cooling properly, it can lead to spoiled food. This guide helps you identify and fix common cooling issues.</p>

        <h2>Tools Needed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Screwdriver</li>
            <li>Multimeter</li>
            <li>Replacement thermostat or fan (if needed)</li>
            <li>Cleaning cloth</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Unplug the refrigerator before starting any inspection.</li>
            <li>Check the thermostat setting; ensure it’s set correctly.</li>
            <li>Clean the condenser coils at the back or bottom of the fridge.</li>
            <li>Inspect the door seal for leaks; replace if torn or loose.</li>
            <li>Listen for the evaporator fan; replace if it’s not running.</li>
            <li>Test the compressor; if faulty, call a professional for replacement.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Do not overload the fridge; proper airflow is essential.</li>
            <li>Regularly clean coils to maintain efficiency.</li>
            <li>Keep the fridge door closed as much as possible.</li>
        </ul>

